---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const post = {
  title: 'Why Most Service Businesses Fail Online (And What Actually Works)',
  category: 'Strategy',
  publishedAt: 'February 12, 2026',
  readTime: '5 min read',
  excerpt: 'The common mistakes we see across every industry — and the framework we use to fix them.',
};

const postId = 'POST-001';

const relatedPosts = [
  {
    id: 'POST-002',
    title: 'Why Most Google Ads Accounts Plateau After Month 3',
    excerpt: 'The structural patterns we see in stalled accounts, and the levers that consistently move them.',
    category: 'Paid Ads',
    categoryColor: 'green',
    publishedAt: 'January 28, 2026',
    image: '/images/blog/google ads plateau after month 3.png',
    slug: 'google-ads-plateau',
  },
  {
    id: 'POST-003',
    title: "Local SEO in 2026: What's Changed and What Still Works",
    excerpt: 'The tactics that have faded and the fundamentals that keep driving rankings for service businesses.',
    category: 'SEO',
    categoryColor: 'gold',
    publishedAt: 'January 14, 2026',
    image: '/images/blog/local seo in 2026.png',
    slug: 'local-seo-2026',
  },
  {
    id: 'POST-004',
    title: 'What Makes a Service Business Website Actually Convert',
    excerpt: "Speed, structure, and trust signals — the three things that separate websites that generate leads from ones that don't.",
    category: 'Web',
    categoryColor: 'blue',
    publishedAt: 'December 18, 2025',
    image: '/images/blog/what makes a service website convert.png',
    slug: 'service-business-website-conversion',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={`${post.title} — Railshop Blog`} description={post.excerpt}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-bg" aria-hidden="true">
      <svg class="hero-grid-svg" viewBox="0 0 1400 480" fill="none" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid slice">
        <line class="grid-line" x1="350" y1="0" x2="350" y2="480"/>
        <line class="grid-line" x1="700" y1="0" x2="700" y2="480"/>
        <line class="grid-line" x1="1050" y1="0" x2="1050" y2="480"/>
        <line class="grid-line" x1="0" y1="160" x2="1400" y2="160"/>
        <line class="grid-line" x1="0" y1="320" x2="1400" y2="320"/>
        <path class="corner-bracket" d="M 32 24 L 32 60 M 32 24 L 68 24"/>
        <path class="corner-bracket" d="M 1368 456 L 1368 420 M 1368 456 L 1332 456"/>
        <line class="tick-mark" x1="350" y1="468" x2="350" y2="480"/>
        <line class="tick-mark" x1="700" y1="468" x2="700" y2="480"/>
        <line class="tick-mark" x1="1050" y1="468" x2="1050" y2="480"/>
      </svg>
      <div class="hero-glow"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Corner annotations -->
    <div class="hero-annotation hero-annotation--tr" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="anno-code">SYS: BLOG</span>
      <span class="anno-sep">·</span>
      <span class="anno-coord">{postId}</span>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-annotation hero-annotation--bl" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="anno-code">// ARTICLE DETAIL</span>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <!-- Breadcrumb inside hero -->
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/blog" class="breadcrumb-link">Blog</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
        <span class="breadcrumb-current">{post.title}</span>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-left">
          <div class="post-meta">
            <span class="post-cat">{post.category}</span>
            <span class="post-meta-sep">·</span>
            <span class="post-date">{post.publishedAt}</span>
            <span class="post-meta-sep">·</span>
            <span class="post-date">{post.readTime}</span>
          </div>
          <h1 class="hero-headline">{post.title}</h1>
          <p class="post-byline">By the Railshop Team</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <div class="content-wrap">
    <div class="container content-grid">

      <!-- Article body -->
      <article class="main-col">

        <div class="content-block">
          <p>Most service businesses aren't failing online because their work is bad. They're failing because the strategies they're running were designed for companies with six-figure ad budgets, in-house marketing teams, and the patience to wait eighteen months for results. That's not the reality for most owner-operators — and it's not how we think about this either.</p>
          <p>After working across HVAC, home security, landscaping, concrete, and a dozen adjacent trades, we've seen the same patterns play out over and over. Here's what's actually going wrong — and what we've found works instead.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-block">
          <div class="block-header">
            <span class="block-label">// 01</span>
            <h2 class="block-title">The Website Isn't Doing Any Work</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="body-copy">The most common issue we see is a website that exists but doesn't convert. It loads slowly, has no clear call to action, and wasn't built with the customer's decision-making process in mind. It looks fine, but it's not generating leads.</p>
          <p class="body-copy">A service business website has one job: turn a visitor into a call or a form fill. Everything else — the design, the content, the SEO — is in service of that. When we take on a new client, the first thing we do is audit whether the site is actually built to convert. Most of the time, it isn't.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-block">
          <div class="block-header">
            <span class="block-label">// 02</span>
            <h2 class="block-title">The Ads Are Running, But the Foundation Is Wrong</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="body-copy">We see a lot of businesses running Google Ads to a homepage that has no conversion tracking set up, no call tracking, and no way to know what's actually working. Money goes in. Leads may or may not come out. Nobody really knows why.</p>
          <p class="body-copy">Good paid media requires a clean foundation — proper tracking, a converting landing page, and a feedback loop between what the ads say and what the site delivers. Without that, you're essentially guessing. We don't run campaigns until that foundation is in place. It's not the exciting part, but it's what makes the difference between a campaign that scales and one that just burns budget.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-block">
          <div class="block-header">
            <span class="block-label">// 03</span>
            <h2 class="block-title">SEO Is Treated As An Add-On</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="body-copy">Most service businesses either ignore SEO entirely or bolt it on as an afterthought — a few blog posts, some keyword stuffing, and a hope that Google figures it out. That's not how it works anymore.</p>
          <p class="body-copy">Local SEO in particular requires a systematic approach: service area pages built for the right terms, a Google Business Profile that's actively managed, citations that are consistent across the web, and content that actually answers the questions your customers are typing into search. Done right, it becomes your highest-margin lead channel. Done wrong, it's just overhead.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="content-block">
          <div class="block-header">
            <span class="block-label">// 04</span>
            <h2 class="block-title">What Actually Works</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="body-copy">The businesses we've seen grow consistently share a few things in common. They have a website built to convert. They run paid ads with proper tracking and a clear feedback loop. They invest in local SEO as a long-term asset, not a quick fix. And they treat their digital presence as an integrated system — not a collection of disconnected tactics.</p>
          <p class="body-copy">None of this is complicated. But it requires doing the fundamentals well, being honest about what the data is saying, and being willing to invest in the right order. That's what we help service businesses do.</p>
          <p class="body-copy">If you want to talk through where your program stands, <a href="/contact#hubspot-meetings">book a call</a>. We'll give you an honest read — no sales pitch, no fluff.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Inline subscribe -->
        <div class="inline-subscribe">
          <div class="inline-subscribe-copy">
            <p class="inline-subscribe-prompt">Posts like this, weekly. No fluff.</p>
            <span class="inline-subscribe-helper">No spam. Unsubscribe anytime.</span>
          </div>
          <form name="newsletter-signup" method="POST" netlify class="inline-subscribe-form">
            <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="newsletter-signup" />
            <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required class="inline-subscribe-input" />
            <button type="submit" class="inline-subscribe-btn">Subscribe</button>
          </form>
        </div>

      </article>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <aside class="sidebar">

        <!-- About -->
        <div class="sidebar-card">
          <p class="sidebar-eyebrow">// ABOUT THE AUTHORS</p>
          <div class="sidebar-body-wrap">
            <p class="sidebar-body">Railshop is a boutique digital growth agency for service businesses. Everything we publish comes from direct experience managing paid media, SEO, and web programs for clients across HVAC, landscaping, home security, and more.</p>
            <a href="/about" class="sidebar-text-link">
              Meet the team
              <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- CTA -->
        <div class="sidebar-card sidebar-card--cta">
          <div class="sidebar-cta-status">
            <span class="sidebar-cta-dot"></span>
            <span class="sidebar-cta-label">Taking new clients</span>
          </div>
          <p class="sidebar-cta-heading">Work with us</p>
          <p class="sidebar-body">Book a no-commitment call to discuss your digital program and see what's possible.</p>
          <a href="/contact#hubspot-meetings" class="sidebar-cta-btn">
            Book a Call
            <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Back link -->
        <a href="/blog" class="sidebar-back-link">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/>
          </svg>
          All posts
        </a>

      </aside>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Related Posts -->
  <section class="related-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="related-header">
        <span class="related-label">// RELATED READING</span>
        <div class="related-rule"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="related-grid">
        {relatedPosts.map((rp) => (
          <a href={`/blog/${rp.slug}`} class="related-card">
            <div class="related-image">
              <img src={rp.image} alt="" class="related-image-img" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
              <div class="card-hud" aria-hidden="true">
                <span class="hud-id">{rp.id}</span>
                <span class="hud-cat">{rp.category}</span>
              </div>
              <span class="img-corner img-corner--tl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="img-corner img-corner--tr" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="img-corner img-corner--bl" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span class="img-corner img-corner--br" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            </div>
            <div class="related-content">
              <span class="related-date">{rp.publishedAt}</span>
              <h3 class="related-title">{rp.title}</h3>
              <p class="related-excerpt">{rp.excerpt}</p>
              <span class="related-cta">
                Read post
                <svg width="10" height="10" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
              </span>
            </div>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Hero ─────────────────────────────────────── */
  .hero {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .hero-bg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .hero-grid-svg {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .grid-line {
    stroke: var(--border);
    stroke-width: 1;
    opacity: 0.4;
  }

  .corner-bracket {
    stroke: var(--border);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
    opacity: 0.35;
  }

  .tick-mark {
    stroke: var(--border);
    stroke-width: 1;
    opacity: 0.5;
  }

  .hero-glow {
    position: absolute;
    top: -40px;
    left: -5%;
    width: 50%;
    height: 100%;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at 30% 40%, rgba(56, 182, 255, 0.04) 0%, transparent 65%);
  }

  .hero-annotation {
    position: absolute;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-3);
    opacity: 0.4;
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .hero-annotation--tr { top: 20px; right: 32px; }
  .hero-annotation--bl { bottom: 20px; left: 32px; }
  .anno-code { color: var(--blue); opacity: 0.8; }
  .anno-sep  { opacity: 0.3; }

  /* Breadcrumb */
  .breadcrumb {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 20px 0;
    font-size: 12px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .breadcrumb-link { color: var(--text-3); transition: color 0.15s; text-decoration: none; }
  .breadcrumb-link:hover { color: var(--blue); }
  .breadcrumb-sep { color: var(--border-2); }
  .breadcrumb-current {
    color: var(--text-3);
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
    white-space: nowrap;
    max-width: 480px;
  }

  /* Hero inner */
  .hero-inner {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 48px 0 60px;
  }

  .hero-left {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0;
  }

  /* Post meta row */
  .post-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .post-cat {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--blue);
    background: rgba(56, 182, 255, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(56, 182, 255, 0.2);
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 3px 8px;
  }

  .post-meta-sep {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--border-2);
  }

  .post-date {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-3);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .hero-headline {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3.5vw, 44px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--text-2);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    max-width: 760px;
  }

  .post-byline {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-3);
    opacity: 0.45;
  }

  /* ── Content ──────────────────────────────────── */
  .content-wrap { padding: 64px 0 80px; }

  .content-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 280px;
    gap: 64px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .main-col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 48px;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  /* Content blocks */
  .content-block {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .block-header {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 6px;
    padding-bottom: 14px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .block-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--blue);
    opacity: 0.65;
  }

  .block-title {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-2);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .body-copy {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--text-3);
    line-height: 1.85;
  }

  .body-copy a {
    color: var(--blue);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }

  /* ── Sidebar ──────────────────────────────────── */
  .sidebar {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 16px;
    position: sticky;
    top: 88px;
  }

  .sidebar-card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 2px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .sidebar-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 8px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--blue);
    opacity: 0.65;
    padding: 10px 16px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: block;
  }

  .sidebar-body-wrap {
    padding: 16px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .sidebar-body {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-3);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .sidebar-text-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--blue);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: gap 0.15s;
  }

  .sidebar-text-link:hover { gap: 9px; }

  /* CTA card */
  .sidebar-card--cta {
    padding: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    background: var(--surface-2);
  }

  .sidebar-cta-status {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 7px;
  }

  .sidebar-cta-dot {
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--green);
    animation: ctapulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  @keyframes ctapulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
    50%       { opacity: 0.25; }
  }

  .sidebar-cta-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--green);
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .sidebar-cta-heading {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-2);
  }

  .sidebar-cta-btn {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 6px;
    background: var(--blue);
    color: #111315;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 13px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 10px 16px;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-top: 4px;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  :global([data-theme="light"]) .sidebar-cta-btn { color: #FFFFFF; }
  .sidebar-cta-btn:hover { opacity: 0.88; }

  /* Back link */
  .sidebar-back-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--text-3);
    opacity: 0.45;
    text-decoration: none;
    padding: 4px 0;
    transition: opacity 0.15s, color 0.15s;
  }

  .sidebar-back-link:hover { opacity: 1; color: var(--text-2); }

  /* ── Related Posts ────────────────────────────── */
  .related-section {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 56px 0 72px;
  }

  .related-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
  }

  .related-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--blue);
    opacity: 0.65;
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .related-rule {
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
  }

  .related-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .related-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .related-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-2);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .related-image {
    position: relative;
    height: 160px;
    background: var(--surface-3);
    overflow: hidden;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .related-image-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: center;
    display: block;
    transition: transform 0.4s ease;
  }

  .related-card:hover .related-image-img { transform: scale(1.03); }

  .related-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 8px;
    padding: 18px 20px 20px;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .related-date {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-3);
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .related-title {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-2);
    line-height: 1.35;
    transition: color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .related-card:hover .related-title { color: var(--blue); }

  .related-excerpt {
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--text-3);
    line-height: 1.75;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .related-cta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 5px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-3);
    margin-top: 4px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .related-card:hover .related-cta {
    color: var(--blue);
    transform: translateX(3px);
  }

  /* HUD overlay */
  .card-hud {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    padding: 6px 10px;
    background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(17,19,21,0.85) 0%, transparent 100%);
  }

  .hud-id {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: rgba(248, 250, 252, 0.5);
  }

  .hud-cat {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--text-2);
    background: rgba(42, 47, 51, 0.8);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-2);
    border-radius: 2px;
